<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<mvt:item name="html_profile" />

<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8">
	<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
	<base href="&mvt:global:basehref;" />
	<mvt:if expr="NOT ISNULL l.settings:page:title">
		<title>&mvt:page:title;</title>
	<mvt:else>
		<title>&mvt:store:name;</title>
	</mvt:if>
	<mvt:if expr="g.useDevResources EQ 1"><mvt:item name="head" param="css_list_dev" /><mvt:else><mvt:item name="head" param="css_list" /></mvt:if>
	<mvt:item name="head" param="head_tag" />
<mvt:comment>
	Checkout V2 staging template. Inactive only. Do not assign over OCST.
	Legacy parity inspected before this repair:
	- ocst.mvt wraps <mvt:item name="customer" /> and <mvt:item name="basket" />.
	- Information fields confirmed in ocst-customer.mvt: ShipFirstName, ShipLastName,
	  ShipEmail, ShipPhone, ShipCompany, ShipFax, ShipAddress1, ShipAddress2,
	  ShipCity, ShipState, ShipStateSelect, ShipCountry, ShipZip, ShipID;
	  BillFirstName, BillLastName, BillEmail, BillPhone, BillCompany, BillFax,
	  BillAddress1, BillAddress2, BillCity, BillState, BillStateSelect,
	  BillCountry, BillZip, BillID; register_password.
	- Shipping/review action parity confirmed in ocst-customer.mvt: Action is assigned
	  to ORDR, ORDR,SHIP,CTAX,AUTH, or PAL2 continuation flow; form action uses
	  l.settings:url / g.Secure_SessionURL.
	- Shipping method selection is confirmed in osel.mvt, not OCST:
	  ShippingMethod is rendered from sorted_methods/shippingmethods and posts to OPAY.
	- Payment parity confirmed in ocst-mivapay.mvt: ResponseXML, ResponseSignature,
	  MivaPay_Frame target behavior, and gateway script must remain backend-owned.
	- Payment method radio selection is confirmed in osel.mvt, not OCST:
	  PaymentMethod is rendered from paymentmethods before gateway-specific handling.
	- Basket/review summary confirmed in ocst-basket.mvt: ReadyTheme contentsection
	  checkout_basket_summary remains backend-owned.
	TODO: preserve those backend items/field names exactly during staging integration;
	do not wire V2 checkout fields until the copied staging OCST item assignments are confirmed.
</mvt:comment>
</head>
<body id="js-&mvte:page:code;">
	<mvt:item name="hdft" param="global_header" />
	<mvt:item name="hdft" param="header" />

<main class="sd2-v2-checkout" data-v2-checkout>
	<header class="sd2-v2-checkout-hero">
		<p class="sd2-kicker">Checkout</p>
		<h1>Secure Checkout</h1>
		<p>Information, shipping, payment, and review stay backed by Miva.</p>
	</header>

	<nav class="sd2-v2-checkout-steps" aria-label="Checkout progress">
		<ol>
			<li class="is-current"><span>1</span><strong>Information</strong></li>
			<li><span>2</span><strong>Shipping</strong></li>
			<li><span>3</span><strong>Payment</strong></li>
			<li><span>4</span><strong>Review</strong></li>
		</ol>
	</nav>

	<form class="sd2-v2-checkout__layout" method="post" action="&mvte:url;">
		<input type="hidden" name="Action" value="&mvte:action;">
		<div class="sd2-v2-checkout__main">
			<section class="sd2-v2-checkout-panel" aria-labelledby="sd2-v2-checkout-info-title">
				<header><p class="sd2-kicker">Step 1</p><h2 id="sd2-v2-checkout-info-title">Information</h2></header>
				<mvt:comment>
					Confirmed information field parity lives in ocst-customer.mvt:
					Ship*, Bill*, ShipID, BillID, register_password, saved basket fields,
					customer addresses, countries/states items, and PayPal PAL2 gateway flag.
					TODO: render those exact legacy controls after staging OCST item setup.
				</mvt:comment>
				<div class="sd2-v2-validation" role="status" aria-live="polite">
					<p>[Placeholder] Miva customer and address fields render here from legacy checkout logic.</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="sd2-v2-checkout-panel" aria-labelledby="sd2-v2-checkout-ship-title">
				<header><p class="sd2-kicker">Step 2</p><h2 id="sd2-v2-checkout-ship-title">Shipping</h2></header>
				<mvt:comment>
					Confirmed shipping flow: shipping selection belongs to OSEL, where
					ShippingMethod is rendered from sorted_methods/shippingmethods and posts to OPAY.
					Do not wire shipping cards into OCST V2.
				</mvt:comment>
				<p>[Placeholder] Shipping method selection occurs on the verified OSEL step.</p>
			</section>

			<section class="sd2-v2-checkout-panel" aria-labelledby="sd2-v2-checkout-payment-title">
				<header><p class="sd2-kicker">Step 3</p><h2 id="sd2-v2-checkout-payment-title">Payment</h2></header>
				<mvt:comment>
					Confirmed payment parity: ocst-mivapay.mvt owns ResponseXML,
					ResponseSignature, MivaPay_Frame target behavior, and gateway message handling.
					Payment method selection belongs to OSEL paymentmethods. Do not replace
					MivaPay iframe/hidden fields/postMessage/signature flow with custom cards.
				</mvt:comment>
				<p>[Placeholder] Payment selection and gateway UI remain owned by verified OSEL/MivaPay templates.</p>
			</section>

			<section class="sd2-v2-checkout-panel" aria-labelledby="sd2-v2-checkout-review-title">
				<header><p class="sd2-kicker">Step 4</p><h2 id="sd2-v2-checkout-review-title">Review</h2></header>
				<mvt:comment>
					Confirmed review parity: ocst-basket.mvt renders checkout_basket_summary;
					totals, shipping, tax, coupon, and final order review remain Miva-owned.
				</mvt:comment>
				<p>[Placeholder] Final order review renders from Miva checkout review logic.</p>
			</section>
		</div>

		<aside class="sd2-v2-order-summary" aria-labelledby="sd2-v2-checkout-summary-title">
			<h2 id="sd2-v2-checkout-summary-title">Order Summary</h2>
			<mvt:comment>
				Preserves ocst-basket.mvt summary role. ocst-basket.mvt itself only renders
				<mvt:item name="readytheme" param="contentsection('checkout_basket_summary')" />
				(backend-owned, cannot be reproduced as inline tokens). Subtotal/Total tokens and
				the basket:charges iterator (shipping/tax line items) below are the same real
				fields used on BASKV2's order summary, safe to compose here directly.
			</mvt:comment>
			<dl>
				<div><dt>Subtotal</dt><dd>&mvt:basket:formatted_subtotal;</dd></div>
				<mvt:foreach iterator="charge" array="basket:charges">
					<div><dt>&mvt:charge:descrip;</dt><dd>&mvt:charge:formatted_disp_amt;</dd></div>
				</mvt:foreach>
				<div class="sd2-v2-order-summary__total"><dt>Total</dt><dd>&mvt:basket:formatted_total;</dd></div>
			</dl>
			<button class="sd2-btn sd2-btn--primary sd2-btn--wide" type="submit">Place Order</button>
		</aside>
	</form>
</main>

	<mvt:item name="hdft" param="footer" />
	<mvt:item name="hdft" param="global_footer" />
</body>
</html>
